                <h2>Why We Must Boycott Uber</h2>
                <ul class="reason-list">
                    <li><strong>Exploitation of Workers:</strong> Uber drivers face unfair wages, lack of benefits, and poor working conditions.</li>
                    <li><strong>Corporate Greed:</strong> Prioritizing profits over people, Uber continues to increase prices while cutting driver pay.</li>
                    <li><strong>Questionable Alliances:</strong> Partnerships with controversial figures like Gautam Adani raise ethical concerns.</li>
                    <li><strong>Undermining Labor Rights:</strong> Uber's business model actively works against worker protections and collective bargaining.</li>
                    <li><strong>Safety Concerns:</strong> Numerous reports highlight passenger and driver safety issues that go unaddressed.</li>
                    <li><strong>Tax Avoidance:</strong> Uber utilizes complex corporate structures to minimize tax obligations worldwide.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
